						<summary>

						<p>Same wall.</p>						

						<p><hi rend="bold">(Kaṉṉaradēva) Kṛishṇa III: Year 5 = 943-44 A.D.</hi></p>						

						<p>This inscription is damaged and refers to the king as one ‘who took Kachchi and Tañjai’.</p>						

						<p>It records a gift of land by the <hi rend="italic">sabhai</hi> (assembly) of Śiṟṟiṅgūr, a <hi rend="italic">Brahmadēyam</hi> in Kuṟukkaik-kūṟṟam in Malāḍu, as <hi rend="italic">dēvadana</hi> for offerings to the god Tiruppulippagavar of the place. It is stated that the <hi rend="italic">sabhai</hi> had exempted this land from the payment of the levies <hi rend="italic">śilliṟai</hi> and <hi rend="italic">echchōṟu.</hi></p>						

						</summary>
